This paper discusses a graph processing framework that is designed to handle large-scale distributed environments, which suggests that it could fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on iterative computations and data mining, which could place it under the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The use of machine learning algorithms also suggests that it could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the processing of relational data, which could place it under the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of asynchronous processing, which could place it under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
